Package openpas.basics

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Assumption  
    Expressions.Expression<Op extends LogicalOps.LogicalOp>
    Generic interface to represent all supported propositional expressions.
    Expressions.SimpleSentence<OpS extends LogicalOps.LogicalOp,OpE extends LogicalOps.LogicalOp>
    This is the generic interface for defining simple propositional sentences.
    Literal
    A literal is the "atomic" building block of all propositional sentences.
    LogicalOps.Biconditional  
    LogicalOps.BinaryDistributive<OpS extends LogicalOps.LogicalOp,OpE extends LogicalOps.LogicalOp>  
    LogicalOps.LogicalAnd  
    LogicalOps.LogicalConverter  
    LogicalOps.LogicalOp
    Widest definition of a binary logical op.
    LogicalOps.LogicalOr  
    LogicalOps.MaterialImplication  
    LogicalOps.Negation  
    LogicalOps.UnaryOp  
    NumericResolver
    Numeric resolver is a do-all interface for all analytical operations in a PAS system.
    PAS
    This is a class that encapsulates a PAS instance.
    ProbabilityComputer
    This is an interface that is about calculating the probability of a PAS expression.
    PropFactory
    ProbFactory is the main way to acquire new objects and access singletons that implement the various interfaces in OpenPAS.
    Proposition
    This is an empty interface to represent a proposition.
    SymbolicResolver
    This defines operations that relate to finding symbolic solutions to hypotheses in PAS.
